<subSubSection id="D6D06521FFF1FFDF9AE9FF30FC726B46" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" type="description">
<paragraph id="9E7536AAFFF1FFDF9AE9FF30FC726B46" blockId="7.[113,1089,218,404]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">
Body length 
<quantity id="59329B4FFFF1FFDF991CFF37FD416AE6" box="[586,718,219,244]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.15" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="7" pageNumber="722" unit="mm" value="5.15" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="3.8">
3.8 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF1FFDF993DFF37FDF76AE1" bold="true" box="[619,632,220,244]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">–</emphasis>
6.5 mm
</quantity>
. Body completely orange or tibiae and tarsi or head black. Antennomere III about 1.3 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF1FFDF99CFFF17FD296B01" bold="true" box="[665,678,252,276]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">–</emphasis>
1.5 times longer than anntenomere II. Pronotum 1.6 
<emphasis id="ACBEEAB8FFF1FFDF9BA9FEF7FE836B21" bold="true" box="[255,268,284,308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">–</emphasis>
2.0 times as wide as long, covered with almost indistinct to fine dense punctures Aedeagus ventrally with long projection from basal part directed anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="06F12A2FFFF1FFDF98F7FED0FC7F6B46" box="[929,1008,315,339]" captionStart="Figs 66–69" captionStartId="26.[151,188,1519,1538]" captionTargetBox="[216,1055,416,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-45@26.[207,1071,413,1499]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figs 66–69.Aedeagus (a – dorsal view; b – lateral view; ventral view). 66 – Hesperopenna vietnamica (Medvedev, 2000) (paratype); 67 – H. antennalis (Kimoto, 1989); 68 – H. minor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype); 69 – H. bicolor (Kimoto, 1989) (paratype). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5740073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5740073/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="722">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
